The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Friday, August 08, 2003 				 Omar Sharif gets jail term
																								Paris, Aug. 7 (Reuters): Movie legend Omar Sharif has been given a one-month suspended prison sentence for hitting a police officer in a casino in suburban Paris last month, a court official said today.																								The Egyptian actor, best known for his role in the 1965 epic Doctor Zhivago, was also fined 1,500 euros for violence towards a police officer, a spokeswoman for the Pontoise criminal court said. 
